     Phase 4: Remote Browser Isolation (Months 10-12)

     Objective: Zero-trust web browsing via containerized desktop streaming

     Components:

     1. Kasm Workspaces for containerized desktop streaming
       - File: vendor/kasm/ (submodule from https://github.com/kasmtech)
       - Deploy: Docker-based browser containers with KasmVNC
       - Use case: Analyst browsing of suspicious URLs, safe web research
     2. Dangerzone for document sanitization
       - File: vendor/dangerzone/ (submodule from https://github.com/freedomofpress/dangerzone)
       - Pipeline: Untrusted PDF/Office → gVisor sandbox → pixelation → safe PDF
       - Integration: REST API for automated processing
     3. BrowserBox or Waterfox for local isolation
       - File: vendor/browserbox/ (reference architecture)
       - Deploy as alternative to Kasm for lightweight use cases

     Deliverables:
     - Remote browser portal (src/frontend/browser_isolation.html)
     - Document sanitization API (src/api/sanitize_document.py)
     - Automated URL detonation in Kasm container
